1
00:00:07,652 --> 00:00:09,608
Welcome your customer.

2
00:00:14,047 --> 00:00:16,433
Singer and actor.

3
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,884
Oh my God.

4
00:00:17,884 --> 00:00:20,106
Welcome your customer.

5
00:00:23,254 --> 00:00:25,031
Hey, In Guk!

6
00:00:25,031 --> 00:00:26,204
Welcome your customer.

7
00:00:26,204 --> 00:00:27,639
[Seo In Guk - Singer and Actor]

8
00:00:27,639 --> 00:00:30,063
Hey, we're so busy.

9
00:00:30,063 --> 00:00:32,304
Welcome your customer.

10
00:00:34,306 --> 00:00:36,815
Where can I sit?

11
00:00:36,815 --> 00:00:38,605
- It's Seo In Guk!
- Are you here for dinner?

12
00:00:38,605 --> 00:00:40,313
- Seo In Guk!
- Yes?

13
00:00:40,313 --> 00:00:42,342
Wow, he's so handsome.

14
00:00:42,342 --> 00:00:44,194
Is it Seo In Guk?

15
00:00:44,194 --> 00:00:45,896
Yeah, it's Seo In Guk.

16
00:00:45,896 --> 00:00:48,876
He really is handsome.

17
00:00:49,839 --> 00:00:51,209
- Hey, In Guk.
- Yeah?

18
00:00:51,209 --> 00:00:53,582
- We're so busy right now.
- Yeah.

19
00:00:53,582 --> 00:00:55,488
Can you help us clean up?

20
00:00:55,488 --> 00:00:57,836
- But I'm a customer.
- Please, just this once.

21
00:00:57,836 --> 00:01:00,159
- I even got you a gift.
- Oh well.

22
00:01:02,897 --> 00:01:04,597
How can I help?

23
00:01:04,597 --> 00:01:06,501
We need to clear these first.

24
00:01:06,501 --> 00:01:10,003
[The Aftermath of the Dinner Rush]

25
00:01:10,003 --> 00:01:11,471
- Everything.
- How do I clear them?

26
00:01:11,471 --> 00:01:12,785
- Come here.
- Are you serious?

27
00:01:12,785 --> 00:01:14,758
Yeah, come here.

28
00:01:14,758 --> 00:01:15,759
- Come here.
- Okay.

29
00:01:15,759 --> 00:01:17,234
[Is This For Real?]

30
00:01:20,681 --> 00:01:22,549
Hello!

31
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:24,617
- Hello.
- Hello.

32
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:26,676
We've got a new helper.

33
00:01:26,676 --> 00:01:27,754
Oh, egg.

34
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,278
[Communication Error!]

35
00:01:29,278 --> 00:01:31,757
Plain rice.

36
00:01:32,310 --> 00:01:34,323
Okay, put on your gloves.

37
00:01:34,323 --> 00:01:35,323
Okay.

38
00:01:35,323 --> 00:01:37,196
- There we go.
- Okay.

39
00:01:39,038 --> 00:01:40,473
Can you clear all those tables?

40
00:01:40,473 --> 00:01:43,048
Hello, Francine!

41
00:01:43,048 --> 00:01:45,033
Oh, hi! How are you?

42
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:47,997
- Hello, nice to see you again!
- How have you been?

43
00:01:47,997 --> 00:01:49,971
- Hi.
- When did you get here?

44
00:01:49,971 --> 00:01:52,591
- How did you...
- Our new server.

45
00:01:52,591 --> 00:01:54,359
Oh, thank you!

46
00:01:54,359 --> 00:01:56,267
New server? Oh, thank you.

47
00:01:57,400 --> 00:02:03,701
[The Brothers]

48
00:02:05,024 --> 00:02:07,594
[New Part-Timer?]

49
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,494
Where do I need to clean...

50
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:25,813
[Starts Anyway...]

51
00:02:32,547 --> 00:02:34,165
[I'm a Customer...]
Tables 3, 1.

52
00:02:34,165 --> 00:02:37,784
Kare-kare, palabok,
sinigang, inasal, gising-gising.

53
00:02:41,873 --> 00:02:44,298
Wow, they're swamped.

54
00:02:44,298 --> 00:02:47,201
[Accepts His Fate...]

55
00:02:53,946 --> 00:02:57,339
Wow, no time to even say hi.

56
00:02:57,339 --> 00:02:59,513
You guys are super busy!

57
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:00,748
It's my first day as well.

58
00:03:00,748 --> 00:03:03,044
- Oh, today is your first day?
- Yeah.

59
00:03:05,024 --> 00:03:07,153
- Hi.
- Hi.

60
00:03:07,153 --> 00:03:09,622
[Plates Piling Up]

61
00:03:09,622 --> 00:03:12,003
[All Clean!]

62
00:03:12,003 --> 00:03:13,004
- Ji!
- Yeah?

63
00:03:13,004 --> 00:03:14,216
Is there a cloth?

64
00:03:14,216 --> 00:03:16,329
To wipe the table.

65
00:03:16,329 --> 00:03:19,021
[Who is he?]
Give me a sec, I need to find it.

66
00:03:19,021 --> 00:03:20,273
Hi.

67
00:03:20,273 --> 00:03:21,784
Hello.

68
00:03:22,803 --> 00:03:25,360
Okay, I'll make one for you.

69
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,408
[Working Non-Stop!]

70
00:03:28,408 --> 00:03:30,843
Whoa, they're busy!

71
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:32,935
Ji!

72
00:03:32,935 --> 00:03:34,014
Ji.

73
00:03:34,014 --> 00:03:36,127
Ah, someone, this guy is calling.

74
00:03:36,127 --> 00:03:37,862
A guy in a black hat.

75
00:03:37,862 --> 00:03:39,909
- Black hat? Okay.
- Yeah.

76
00:03:39,909 --> 00:03:41,600
- Here's your cloth.
- Thanks.

77
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,801
Chef said he's asking for you.

78
00:03:43,801 --> 00:03:45,425
- This guy.
- How can I help you?

79
00:03:45,425 --> 00:03:47,084
Is my food coming?

80
00:03:47,084 --> 00:03:48,573
One moment, please.

81
00:03:48,573 --> 00:03:50,657
I got hired all of a sudden.

82
00:03:51,264 --> 00:03:53,167
- Excuse me.
- Yes, go ahead.

83
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:55,096
- We ordered Coke Zero, but...
- Not out yet?

84
00:03:55,096 --> 00:03:56,570
- Yeah.
- How rude.

85
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:59,373
- I'll bring it right away.
- Thank you.

86
00:03:59,373 --> 00:04:01,825
- I just spoke with Seo In Guk!
- Awesome.

87
00:04:03,755 --> 00:04:05,745
Sorry, where is Zero Coke?

88
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:07,113
- Coke Zero?
- Yeah, Coke Zero.

89
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:08,454
I am not sure.

90
00:04:08,454 --> 00:04:09,939
Okay.

91
00:04:09,939 --> 00:04:12,051
Ah, In Guk, right here.

92
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:13,855
- Oh, it's here?
- Who should I give it to?

93
00:04:13,855 --> 00:04:15,271
Here, here.

94
00:04:17,685 --> 00:04:19,192
- Is this the right one?
- Yes.

95
00:04:19,192 --> 00:04:21,160
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

96
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,552
[One After Another]
Oh, hello!

97
00:04:23,552 --> 00:04:25,076
Table for three?

98
00:04:25,076 --> 00:04:28,534
Please have a seat here.
Oh, I'll wipe the table for you.

99
00:04:28,534 --> 00:04:31,370
You know what? I came here as a customer.

100
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:34,930
For real.

101
00:04:34,930 --> 00:04:36,843
Oh yeah, that's a customer's outfit.

102
00:04:36,843 --> 00:04:39,512
Right? I'm not wearing the uniform.

103
00:04:39,512 --> 00:04:41,714
[For the Nth Time]
[He's a Customer, Not a Server]

104
00:04:41,714 --> 00:04:44,635
- You can sit here.
- Okay, thank you.

105
00:04:44,635 --> 00:04:46,269
I'll sit here.

106
00:04:49,723 --> 00:04:51,241
[Now Enjoying His Fate]

107
00:04:51,241 --> 00:04:54,383
If you don't mind snacking before the meal,
I can bring some over.

108
00:04:54,383 --> 00:04:55,757
- Yes!
- Yes, thank you!

109
00:04:55,757 --> 00:04:56,958
Water and a napkin, please.

110
00:04:56,958 --> 00:04:58,560
- Water and a napkin.
- Yes.

111
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,811
I'll get you enough napkins.

112
00:04:59,811 --> 00:05:02,035
- You ordered inasal, right?
- And Coke Zero.

113
00:05:02,035 --> 00:05:04,971
- Do you want some garlic rice?
- Yes.

114
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:08,808
[Thanks to In Guk]
[The Team's Back In Order]

115
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:10,934
- That's delicious! It's sweet.
- Thank you.

116
00:05:10,934 --> 00:05:12,880
- For your desserts.
- Wow, look at this.

117
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:15,399
[Waiting Becomes Enjoyable with In Guk]
Nice.

118
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,906
- Did you get your Coke Zero?
- Yes!

119
00:05:16,906 --> 00:05:18,661
That's great.

120
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,983
Happy birthday!

121
00:05:21,983 --> 00:05:24,302
- Here's your napkin.
- Thank you so much!

122
00:05:24,302 --> 00:05:27,594
- We're celebrating his birthday today.
- It's his birthday.

123
00:05:27,594 --> 00:05:28,696
- Today?
- Yes!

124
00:05:28,696 --> 00:05:29,958
Yesterday was my birthday.

125
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:32,366
- Wow!
- Really?

126
00:05:32,366 --> 00:05:34,590
- Can you sing a song?
- Yeah. Your name?

127
00:05:34,590 --> 00:05:35,802
- Paolo.
- Paolo?

128
00:05:35,802 --> 00:05:39,672
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

129
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:42,375
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

130
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:45,612
<i>♪ Happy birthday, my friend Paolo ♪</i>

131
00:05:45,612 --> 00:05:48,258
- Thank you.
<i>- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

132
00:05:50,994 --> 00:05:52,825
So nice!

133
00:05:52,825 --> 00:05:55,450
- Have a happy birthday, Paolo!
- Cheers!

134
00:05:55,450 --> 00:05:59,464
- Happy birthday, Paolo!
- Happy birthday!

135
00:06:00,121 --> 00:06:02,929
I think things are going back to normal.

136
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:06,265
[Server Mode Off, Customer Mode On]

137
00:06:06,265 --> 00:06:07,700
He's going to have his meal now.

138
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:10,198
Oh, he is finally going to have it.

139
00:06:10,198 --> 00:06:11,810
What's funny is...

140
00:06:11,810 --> 00:06:15,442
I went in there, put on my gloves,
and rolled up my sleeves,

141
00:06:15,442 --> 00:06:19,057
then everyone in there
just naturally put me to work.

142
00:06:19,057 --> 00:06:21,481
I will just have to clean up everything.

143
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:22,649
Is that okay?

144
00:06:22,649 --> 00:06:23,916
Ah, this guy calling.

145
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:25,658
A guy in a black hat.

146
00:06:25,658 --> 00:06:27,353
- Black hat? Okay.
- Yeah.

147
00:06:30,524 --> 00:06:35,640
That's not how Francine looked
when she sang "My Love" with me.

148
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,609
She must be so tired.

149
00:06:37,609 --> 00:06:40,099
Oh, here you are. What do you want?

150
00:06:40,099 --> 00:06:42,046
- Can I order?
- Yeah.

151
00:06:42,046 --> 00:06:47,614
Palabok, inasal, kare-kare, and garlic rice.

152
00:06:47,614 --> 00:06:49,304
Okay. How about your drinks?

153
00:06:49,304 --> 00:06:51,777
- Coke Zero.
- Alright.

154
00:06:52,846 --> 00:06:53,846
Chef?

155
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:56,643
- Can you boil noodles again, please?
- Yeah.

156
00:07:03,312 --> 00:07:06,571
Hot, hot, hot.

157
00:07:06,571 --> 00:07:07,660
Beautiful.

158
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:09,212
Two palaboks.

159
00:07:09,212 --> 00:07:10,797
This is your palabok.

160
00:07:10,797 --> 00:07:13,667
- Here's your palabok.
- Ah, okay.

161
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:15,013
How is it?

162
00:07:15,013 --> 00:07:16,253
Is it good?

163
00:07:16,253 --> 00:07:17,770
It's savory.

164
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,907
I love the shrimp aroma.

165
00:07:22,615 --> 00:07:24,644
It tastes familiar, yet unfamiliar.

166
00:07:24,644 --> 00:07:25,990
You're right.

167
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:29,255
One, two, three, four.

168
00:07:29,255 --> 00:07:31,256
Kare-kare!

169
00:07:33,197 --> 00:07:34,449
Kare-kare.

170
00:07:34,449 --> 00:07:36,056
- Here you go, In Guk.
- Thank you.

171
00:07:36,056 --> 00:07:37,412
Sure.

172
00:07:50,153 --> 00:07:52,405
Why is this so good?

173
00:07:52,405 --> 00:07:56,108
[Kare-kare Keeping His Spoon Busy]

174
00:07:57,110 --> 00:07:58,877
It's so delicious!

175
00:08:00,007 --> 00:08:01,559
Where's our other server?

176
00:08:01,559 --> 00:08:03,161
He's gone.

177
00:08:03,161 --> 00:08:04,529
No, he ate.

178
00:08:04,529 --> 00:08:06,642
Oh, he's eating!

179
00:08:06,642 --> 00:08:07,882
Why?

180
00:08:07,882 --> 00:08:09,788
He's a server!

181
00:08:10,790 --> 00:08:12,754
Ji, inasal.

182
00:08:12,754 --> 00:08:14,443
Oh, okay.

183
00:08:15,557 --> 00:08:17,630
- Here it is.
- Oh, thank you.

184
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:19,705
I'm sorry for the wait.

185
00:08:19,705 --> 00:08:23,170
- Oh my gosh, I'm satisfied already.
- I can tell Mom's falling for him.

186
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,904
I got butterflies too. He's so handsome.

187
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:27,073
It's like a fairy showed up.

188
00:08:27,073 --> 00:08:29,041
[She's a Big Fan of Ji]

189
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:35,081
[Super In Love with Ji]

190
00:08:35,081 --> 00:08:37,745
[Switched to VIP Seat]

191
00:08:37,745 --> 00:08:38,974
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

192
00:08:38,974 --> 00:08:40,486
Got everything but the garlic rice?

193
00:08:40,486 --> 00:08:43,056
[A Dream Come True!]

194
00:08:43,056 --> 00:08:45,057
You're like a young girl again, Mom!

195
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:47,438
- She is a girl.
- Right.

196
00:08:47,438 --> 00:08:49,495
You're probably his biggest fan here.

197
00:08:49,495 --> 00:08:50,941
That's right.

198
00:08:52,398 --> 00:08:55,568
[After the Chaos...]

199
00:08:57,471 --> 00:09:00,707
[Finally Getting Some Breather]

200
00:09:01,774 --> 00:09:03,532
We don't have any new orders anymore?

201
00:09:03,532 --> 00:09:06,357
No more. They're just finishing up.

202
00:09:06,357 --> 00:09:09,147
That's the best news ever!

203
00:09:13,364 --> 00:09:15,355
- Things are slowing down now?
- Yeah.

204
00:09:15,355 --> 00:09:16,722
How was the taste?

205
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,130
It was good!

206
00:09:18,130 --> 00:09:19,258
This is so tasty.

207
00:09:19,258 --> 00:09:20,883
- Kare-kare?
- Yeah.

208
00:09:20,883 --> 00:09:23,163
- You know what's important?
- What?

209
00:09:23,163 --> 00:09:25,321
I didn't get to try it.

210
00:09:25,321 --> 00:09:27,167
Nothing? Not even one dish?

211
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:28,414
I tried one chicken leg.

212
00:09:28,414 --> 00:09:30,426
Oh, really?

213
00:09:30,426 --> 00:09:32,155
Were there a lot of customers today?

214
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:34,496
The dinner rush hit hard
when I got here, right?

215
00:09:34,496 --> 00:09:38,644
- That's when our restaurant was falling apart.
- Really?

216
00:09:41,571 --> 00:09:43,995
Sweetheart!

217
00:09:43,995 --> 00:09:45,674
How are you?

218
00:09:45,674 --> 00:09:47,146
Hey!

219
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:52,158
Are you tired?
Do you want some calamansi juice?

220
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:53,392
I'm okay.

221
00:09:53,392 --> 00:09:55,262
Good job.

222
00:09:55,262 --> 00:09:57,364
Thank you.

223
00:09:57,364 --> 00:09:58,965
Geez.

224
00:09:58,965 --> 00:10:02,096
It's like a tsunami swept through.

225
00:10:02,096 --> 00:10:05,010
Wow, that drained me.

226
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:06,634
Oh yeah.

227
00:10:06,634 --> 00:10:09,103
- I'm okay.
- But at least it's just physical.

228
00:10:09,103 --> 00:10:11,633
We weren't stressed out.

229
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:14,058
No one's fought yet.

230
00:10:14,058 --> 00:10:15,326
Someone has to fight?

231
00:10:15,326 --> 00:10:18,702
- Like when you want to kill each other.
- So it's just stress.

232
00:10:18,702 --> 00:10:20,770
- But...
- I think I was just stressed internally.

233
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:23,468
Because like,
I was juggling so many pots there.

234
00:10:23,468 --> 00:10:24,469
Yeah.

235
00:10:24,469 --> 00:10:28,060
And then later when you sleep,
you kind of like, "Okay..."

236
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:30,463
Oh my God, you know what?
When I sleep at night,

237
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:34,900
the moment I close my eyes and I dream,
I still dream about cooking.

238
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,802
I dream about the palabok.

239
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:39,100
I dream about the gising-gising.

240
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:42,441
It's like I'm living in a simulation.

241
00:10:45,389 --> 00:10:47,564
- Who is he?
- He's Ji's friend, right?

242
00:10:47,564 --> 00:10:49,788
- What's his name?
- Seo In Guk.

243
00:10:49,788 --> 00:10:51,217
- Seo In Guk?
- Yeah.

244
00:10:51,217 --> 00:10:54,020
So, he will work with us?

245
00:10:54,020 --> 00:10:56,829
Because I was
kinda ordering him around earlier.

246
00:10:56,829 --> 00:11:00,092
I said, "Since I'm going to do this,
you do this and do that."

247
00:11:00,092 --> 00:11:02,590
And he's like...

248
00:11:02,590 --> 00:11:03,863
Turns out he's a customer.

249
00:11:03,863 --> 00:11:05,398
I thought he was here to help out.

250
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:07,784
That's why I was surprised.

251
00:11:07,784 --> 00:11:10,191
"Why are you suddenly sitting down?"

252
00:11:11,232 --> 00:11:12,728
Oh, take this.

253
00:11:12,728 --> 00:11:14,518
- What is this?
- So...

254
00:11:14,518 --> 00:11:16,594
It's alcohol. It's champagne.

255
00:11:16,594 --> 00:11:17,866
- Really?
- Yeah.

256
00:11:17,866 --> 00:11:21,347
- Why don't you give it to Chef yourself?
- Oh, should I?

257
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:24,111
- 'Cause it's also my first day.
- Oh really?

258
00:11:24,111 --> 00:11:27,887
- Oh, this place has been open since before?
- Yeah, this is...

259
00:11:27,887 --> 00:11:33,226
- She's like Kumusta's boss.
- Boss?

260
00:11:33,226 --> 00:11:34,333
Hi, boss.

261
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,112
- Hello.
- My name is In Guk.

262
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,230
I am Jodi. Nice to meet you.

263
00:11:38,230 --> 00:11:39,338
Me too.

264
00:11:39,338 --> 00:11:40,833
- This is our chef.
- Yes.

265
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,696
Thank you for helping us.

266
00:11:43,665 --> 00:11:45,945
- What's this?
- Champagne.

267
00:11:45,945 --> 00:11:47,479
- Champagne!
- Yes.

268
00:11:47,479 --> 00:11:49,231
Thanks!

269
00:11:49,231 --> 00:11:50,922
Thank you.

270
00:11:50,922 --> 00:11:52,284
Thanks.

271
00:11:52,284 --> 00:11:54,875
Thank you.

272
00:11:54,875 --> 00:11:57,901
Oh, champagne!

273
00:11:57,901 --> 00:11:59,586
Hey, can I get the bill?

274
00:11:59,586 --> 00:12:02,000
Ah, the bill, the bill.

275
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,768
- Table number?
- Actually, he said free.

276
00:12:03,768 --> 00:12:06,060
- Yeah, free for you.
- No, it's okay.

277
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:07,121
It's on me!

278
00:12:07,121 --> 00:12:08,528
- No, no.
- It's on him!

279
00:12:08,528 --> 00:12:12,798
In Korea, if we visit a friend at work,

280
00:12:12,798 --> 00:12:15,451
we usually pay ourselves before we leave.

281
00:12:15,451 --> 00:12:18,694
Then can you also pay for our dinner later?

282
00:12:18,694 --> 00:12:22,431
What? I never said yes.

283
00:12:22,431 --> 00:12:24,199
- Okay. Check.
- Okay.

284
00:12:24,199 --> 00:12:25,611
Thank you, sir.

285
00:12:25,611 --> 00:12:28,075
Thank you!

286
00:12:28,075 --> 00:12:30,672
- Goodbye!
- Take care!

287
00:12:30,672 --> 00:12:33,542
- You're our last customer, we're closing now.
- Really?

288
00:12:33,542 --> 00:12:36,279
- Alright, flip the sign please.
- I flip it?

289
00:12:36,279 --> 00:12:37,823
Yeah. Closed.

290
00:12:37,823 --> 00:12:40,343
- Put it out like this.
- Oh, like this?

291
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:42,856
- Good job.
- Thanks. Yeah.

292
00:12:45,842 --> 00:12:48,300
- Okay. Bye, In Guk.
- I'll call you.

293
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:50,063
- Thank you!
- No worries.

294
00:12:51,615 --> 00:12:53,551
Bye!

295
00:12:53,551 --> 00:12:55,864
Ah, we're closed.

296
00:12:55,864 --> 00:12:58,077
- Let's go to eat.
- Yeah, let's go!

297
00:12:58,077 --> 00:13:00,946
[Worked Hard?]

298
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:03,849
[Worked Hard?]
[Eat Harder!]

299
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:08,521
[Authentic K-BBQ]

300
00:13:09,128 --> 00:13:10,796
[Here We Go!]
I think I'm hungry.

301
00:13:10,796 --> 00:13:12,297
Yeah.

302
00:13:14,433 --> 00:13:16,969
Since you came all the way here,

303
00:13:16,969 --> 00:13:18,998
- Yes!
- I'll cook the grilled pork belly for you.

304
00:13:18,998 --> 00:13:22,267
Thank you!

305
00:13:23,086 --> 00:13:25,256
Hungry, hungry!

306
00:13:25,256 --> 00:13:30,543
This type of grilled pork belly
is called pot lid pork belly.

307
00:13:30,543 --> 00:13:33,111
Whoa, I thought it was just a lid.

308
00:13:36,727 --> 00:13:39,818
- Ah, so that's how it's done.
- Yeah.

309
00:13:42,099 --> 00:13:47,271
So is this the proper way
to cook grilled pork belly?

310
00:13:47,271 --> 00:13:50,536
Yes, as the pork fat drips down the grill,

311
00:13:50,536 --> 00:13:54,601
we cook the bean sprouts and kimchi with it.

312
00:13:54,601 --> 00:13:56,836
- Ah, okay.
- That's how...

313
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:59,622
Yeah, it goes like that.

314
00:13:59,622 --> 00:14:01,740
Okay, okay.

315
00:14:04,155 --> 00:14:08,347
This is the first time
we eat together outside of the restaurant.

316
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,715
- Right.
- Not in the restaurant.

317
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:12,784
Oh, it's too bad
you guys couldn't go out for dinner.

318
00:14:16,988 --> 00:14:18,569
[The Warmth of K-Hospitality]
Okay.

319
00:14:18,569 --> 00:14:19,843
- Thank you.
- Yehey!

320
00:14:19,843 --> 00:14:21,293
Okay.

321
00:14:21,293 --> 00:14:23,407
Oh, thank you!

322
00:14:23,407 --> 00:14:27,322
Feel free to eat what I placed on the side.

323
00:14:27,322 --> 00:14:29,201
Okay!

324
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:32,638
[Let's Taste It!]

325
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,985
[Ji's Samgyup 101]

326
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:57,663
[Trying It Ji's Way]

327
00:14:58,887 --> 00:15:00,465
Good.

328
00:15:07,034 --> 00:15:09,649
[Pot Lid Pork Belly]
How was our day today?

329
00:15:09,649 --> 00:15:12,518
Although we had so many...

330
00:15:12,518 --> 00:15:14,965
- Struggles.
- Customers, struggles...

331
00:15:14,965 --> 00:15:20,298
It was my first time
working with everyone today,

332
00:15:20,298 --> 00:15:23,217
and even though things got a little hectic,

333
00:15:23,217 --> 00:15:26,787
I'm glad we managed everything in the end.

334
00:15:26,787 --> 00:15:30,441
Even if it was busy, you were still smiling.

335
00:15:30,441 --> 00:15:31,976
Yeah.

336
00:15:31,976 --> 00:15:33,939
So, it helps.

337
00:15:33,939 --> 00:15:36,514
When you go to the kitchen, you're smiling.

338
00:15:36,514 --> 00:15:37,987
We're stressing out.

339
00:15:37,987 --> 00:15:40,968
You're smiling, so our stress goes down.

340
00:15:40,968 --> 00:15:46,878
But whenever I give you the orders,
you never like it.

341
00:15:48,514 --> 00:15:50,961
Because I'm afraid of you.

342
00:15:50,961 --> 00:15:52,518
You always come with new orders.

343
00:15:52,518 --> 00:15:55,744
"New order! Palabok! Kare-kare!"

344
00:15:55,744 --> 00:15:57,006
Chef!

345
00:15:57,006 --> 00:15:59,458
One palabok, one inasal...

346
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:01,393
Chef! One kare-kare...

347
00:16:01,393 --> 00:16:02,561
- Chef!
- Yes!

348
00:16:02,561 --> 00:16:03,729
- Chef!
- Yes?

349
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:04,763
- Chef!
- Yo.

350
00:16:04,763 --> 00:16:07,322
- Chef!
- I'm afraid of you.

351
00:16:07,322 --> 00:16:09,668
Every time you come, you come with new orders.

352
00:16:09,668 --> 00:16:11,771
A lot of orders!

353
00:16:13,372 --> 00:16:17,182
But I think the customers
really enjoyed the food,

354
00:16:17,182 --> 00:16:18,911
so that felt great.

355
00:16:18,911 --> 00:16:20,941
Yeah!

356
00:16:20,941 --> 00:16:23,315
Do you think you can stay with us
until the end?

357
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:25,517
- Me?
- Yes.

358
00:16:28,972 --> 00:16:31,156
- Oh sure!
- Really?

359
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:32,592
- Yeah!
- Yay!

360
00:16:32,592 --> 00:16:34,060
Yeah.

361
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:35,728
Hello!

362
00:16:35,728 --> 00:16:38,241
- I'm here!
- Arci!

363
00:16:38,887 --> 00:16:40,299
[Yesterday's MVP Arci Joins In]
Hi!

364
00:16:40,299 --> 00:16:41,768
- Hi!
- Hello!

365
00:16:41,768 --> 00:16:43,069
Arci, Ji.

366
00:16:43,069 --> 00:16:46,405
- Hello!
- Hello.

367
00:16:47,229 --> 00:16:48,374
How's today?

368
00:16:48,374 --> 00:16:49,926
Super busy!

369
00:16:49,926 --> 00:16:52,267
So you must be all tired.

370
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:53,346
- Yeah.
- And hungry.

371
00:16:53,346 --> 00:16:56,426
- Hungry.
- Wait, before that...

372
00:16:57,644 --> 00:17:01,966
Before that, let's have this first.

373
00:17:01,966 --> 00:17:05,002
Jell Life carb blocker.

374
00:17:05,002 --> 00:17:06,287
Ah, for losing weight?

375
00:17:06,287 --> 00:17:08,327
So the carbs don't get absorbed by the system.

376
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:10,229
- Can I... is that a gel?
- Yes, yes!

377
00:17:10,229 --> 00:17:11,730
This is all natural.

378
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:16,168
With white kidney bean extract,
collagen, needle mushroom...

379
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:17,726
This is not medicine, by the way.

380
00:17:17,726 --> 00:17:20,334
This is for beauty also.

381
00:17:20,334 --> 00:17:21,890
Where's the grape?

382
00:17:24,666 --> 00:17:27,686
This grilled pork belly
goes perfectly with somaek.

383
00:17:27,686 --> 00:17:30,349
- Somaek?
- I'll show you.

384
00:17:30,349 --> 00:17:33,275
- Soju and beer, mix!
- Beer!

385
00:17:33,275 --> 00:17:35,289
- Yeah.
- Somaek.

386
00:17:35,289 --> 00:17:40,910
If there's no bottle opener,
we do this in Korea.

387
00:17:40,910 --> 00:17:42,527
Amazing!

388
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:47,867
Somaek is all about the ratio.

389
00:17:47,867 --> 00:17:50,048
Usually when you stack the glasses like this,

390
00:17:50,048 --> 00:17:54,139
you fill half with soju.

391
00:17:55,976 --> 00:18:00,758
And then you fill the glass
all the way with beer.

392
00:18:04,422 --> 00:18:07,481
Then you take a shot.

393
00:18:07,481 --> 00:18:08,822
- Oh, it's a shot!
- Here.

394
00:18:08,822 --> 00:18:10,734
Okay, I will try.

395
00:18:11,702 --> 00:18:13,543
Thank you!

396
00:18:13,543 --> 00:18:14,960
Thank you.

397
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,829
- Cheers!
- Well done, everyone!

398
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:18,797
- Cheers!
- You say, "Tagay!"

399
00:18:18,797 --> 00:18:21,033
Tagay!

400
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:23,535
Drink until we drop!

401
00:18:26,405 --> 00:18:29,443
[Instant Relief!]

402
00:18:36,366 --> 00:18:38,183
It's good.

403
00:18:38,718 --> 00:18:40,586
One more.

404
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:43,082
- Ah, one more, okay.
- One more.

405
00:18:45,536 --> 00:18:48,572
Looks like I'll be mixing shots all night!

406
00:18:48,572 --> 00:18:49,894
Here.

407
00:18:50,746 --> 00:18:52,737
Sorry.

408
00:18:52,737 --> 00:18:54,333
Oh, thank you!

409
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,524
Okay. I'm a somaek preacher.

410
00:18:56,524 --> 00:18:58,671
Why is it like this?
Is it one drink after another?

411
00:18:58,671 --> 00:18:59,938
- Yes.
- Is it really like that?

412
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:02,108
You have to drink it like, no pacing?

413
00:19:02,108 --> 00:19:04,409
That wasn't my intention.

414
00:19:05,139 --> 00:19:07,046
Chef asked for one more...

415
00:19:07,046 --> 00:19:08,080
Let's go!

416
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,449
Cheers!

417
00:19:10,449 --> 00:19:14,486
- Cheers.
- This was Chef's plan all along.

418
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:20,025
It's delicious.

419
00:19:21,094 --> 00:19:23,713
As if I'm drinking alcohol. I even did this.

420
00:19:23,713 --> 00:19:27,132
Because that's a sign of respect for them
if you're younger.

421
00:19:29,074 --> 00:19:32,137
- Okay, thank you.
- Chef, get some for me too.

422
00:19:34,151 --> 00:19:36,431
What's "delicious" in Korean?

423
00:19:36,431 --> 00:19:38,950
- "Masisseoyo."
- "Masisseoyo?"

424
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:40,678
"Masisseoyo."

425
00:19:41,792 --> 00:19:44,618
It feels weird that we're eating.

426
00:19:44,618 --> 00:19:46,018
- Yeah.
- And not serving.

427
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:48,838
I'm still working, guys.

428
00:19:48,838 --> 00:19:51,268
- Oh, right.
- I keep mixing shots for you.

429
00:19:51,268 --> 00:19:53,592
- Cook meat, give it to you...
- You're ordering him around!

430
00:19:53,592 --> 00:19:54,726
It's all because of Chef.

431
00:19:54,726 --> 00:19:56,245
You want to sit here?

432
00:19:56,245 --> 00:19:57,619
Isn't it too late?

433
00:19:57,619 --> 00:19:59,843
Okay, do your job.

434
00:19:59,843 --> 00:20:02,974
I think we need to fix our...

435
00:20:02,974 --> 00:20:05,443
- Strategy for tomorrow?
- Strategy, yeah.

436
00:20:05,443 --> 00:20:08,513
So I think that we'll have to...

437
00:20:08,513 --> 00:20:13,290
Let's say, designate a dispatcher
just for the orders.

438
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:15,681
- Yeah.
- Yes, because it was really hard earlier

439
00:20:15,681 --> 00:20:20,197
when all the orders were coming in
and no one was there to cross everything out.

440
00:20:20,197 --> 00:20:22,371
- So we don't know...
- It was very confusing.

441
00:20:22,371 --> 00:20:26,114
Yeah, we're not sure what was already served.

442
00:20:26,114 --> 00:20:31,190
Then I'll try to call
a few friends to help out.

443
00:20:31,987 --> 00:20:34,434
How many?

444
00:20:37,548 --> 00:20:40,405
- How many friends?
- Usually when you hear this,

445
00:20:40,405 --> 00:20:43,074
don't you just say "thank you"?

446
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:44,643
"How many..."

447
00:20:44,643 --> 00:20:46,519
- Thank you, thank you.
- Sure.

448
00:20:46,519 --> 00:20:49,443
Thank you, sorry.

449
00:20:49,443 --> 00:20:50,444
Do you want some more?

450
00:20:50,444 --> 00:20:52,157
[And the night falls...]

451
00:20:53,619 --> 00:20:56,655
[Day 4]

452
00:20:57,344 --> 00:20:59,658
- Hello!
- Hi!

453
00:20:59,658 --> 00:21:01,889
- Hi, Ji!
- Hello!

454
00:21:01,889 --> 00:21:03,095
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

455
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:04,529
Welcome to our kitchen again.

456
00:21:04,529 --> 00:21:06,693
- It's good?
- Perfect.

457
00:21:06,693 --> 00:21:10,223
You need anything? Need help?

458
00:21:11,337 --> 00:21:14,173
- Okay, so we have a new dish for today.
- Okay.

459
00:21:14,173 --> 00:21:16,775
- Which is sisig.
- Sisig.

460
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:18,176
[Today's Menu: Sisig]

461
00:21:18,744 --> 00:21:21,959
[Today's Menu: Sisig]

462
00:21:21,959 --> 00:21:23,532
Sisig is pork head.

463
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:24,783
Is it maskara?

464
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:27,052
- Yes. It's two ways.
- Okay.

465
00:21:27,052 --> 00:21:30,516
And then so what we did is,
we have a soft part here.

466
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:35,193
[Pork Ear &amp; Cheeks]

467
00:21:35,861 --> 00:21:36,862
[Sisig]

468
00:21:36,862 --> 00:21:41,973
[A sizzling, savory dish
of chopped pig's head and liver]

469
00:21:41,973 --> 00:21:45,570
[seasoned with calamansi and chili]

470
00:21:47,234 --> 00:21:49,374
And then we have a crunchy part.

471
00:21:49,374 --> 00:21:52,277
[Deep-Fry Pork Cheeks]

472
00:21:57,978 --> 00:21:59,585
We have a liver sauce.

473
00:21:59,585 --> 00:22:01,704
- Is it pig's liver?
- It's pig's liver.

474
00:22:01,704 --> 00:22:03,288
Okay.

475
00:22:03,288 --> 00:22:08,060
[Boil Pork Liver with Spices and Seasonings]

476
00:22:08,793 --> 00:22:12,964
[Blend Boiled Pork Liver]

477
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:14,517
[Liver Sauce]
Just add calamansi.

478
00:22:14,517 --> 00:22:16,168
Calamansi.

479
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:20,995
Chef, what if the customers ask,
"What's sisig?"

480
00:22:20,995 --> 00:22:26,473
It's pork head that we braised and fried
with liver sauce.

481
00:22:26,473 --> 00:22:29,938
I want you to taste it
so that you know what you're serving.

482
00:22:29,938 --> 00:22:31,089
You eat liver?

483
00:22:31,089 --> 00:22:33,151
Actually, it's my first time trying it.

484
00:22:33,151 --> 00:22:34,286
- Really?
- Yeah.

485
00:22:34,286 --> 00:22:37,110
Okay, there's always a first time.

486
00:22:42,567 --> 00:22:43,995
Here we go.

487
00:22:45,448 --> 00:22:49,267
Tell me what you think, then we can adjust it.

488
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:50,504
How is it?

489
00:22:50,504 --> 00:22:54,062
I think I'm just not used to the liver sauce,
but it's good.

490
00:22:54,062 --> 00:22:55,540
Okay.

491
00:23:02,070 --> 00:23:04,300
Alright, that's a sisig dance.

492
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,962
- Ji, would you like to try?
- Ah, okay.

493
00:23:12,497 --> 00:23:14,192
With rice...

494
00:23:15,550 --> 00:23:17,218
You, uh...

495
00:23:17,218 --> 00:23:18,830
Okay. Alright.

496
00:23:18,830 --> 00:23:23,869
Okay, stop looking at us so that we can focus.

497
00:23:23,869 --> 00:23:26,004
There goes Chef again.

498
00:23:26,004 --> 00:23:27,344
Okay?

499
00:23:30,331 --> 00:23:32,167
Ji, are you ready to open?

500
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:33,585
Yes, I'm ready.

501
00:23:33,585 --> 00:23:36,548
Kindly open the sign outside.

502
00:23:38,984 --> 00:23:40,952
Flip over.

503
00:23:41,509 --> 00:23:44,589
Sisig. Today's new menu.

504
00:23:45,769 --> 00:23:47,425
Okay.

505
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:51,263
Alright.

506
00:23:51,263 --> 00:23:53,632
[12:00 PM]

507
00:23:53,632 --> 00:23:56,268
[Customers Enter]

508
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:02,019
Hello! Welcome.

509
00:24:02,019 --> 00:24:03,142
- Table for two?
- Yes.

510
00:24:03,142 --> 00:24:05,143
You can sit wherever you like.

511
00:24:07,608 --> 00:24:09,954
- Here's your menu.
- Thank you.

512
00:24:09,954 --> 00:24:12,783
- Let me know when you're ready.
- Alright, thank you.

513
00:24:15,755 --> 00:24:17,685
I can't look at him properly.

514
00:24:17,685 --> 00:24:19,090
Me too.

515
00:24:19,820 --> 00:24:21,926
- Heart racing.
- Yeah.

516
00:24:25,008 --> 00:24:28,499
Wow! Why is this place so nice?

517
00:24:30,291 --> 00:24:32,410
- Hello!
- We're two.

518
00:24:32,410 --> 00:24:34,439
- Oh, hello!
- Two?

519
00:24:39,662 --> 00:24:41,746
So cute!

520
00:24:43,649 --> 00:24:45,717
Let me know when you're ready.

521
00:24:47,692 --> 00:24:49,654
What do you want to eat?

522
00:24:50,361 --> 00:24:51,563
I don't want to eat.

523
00:24:51,563 --> 00:24:53,058
Why don't you want to eat?

