00:41:06,926 --> 00:41:09,873
Okay, this is...

793
00:41:09,873 --> 00:41:11,480
What's this? Wow!

794
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,688
- It's for you.
- Shirataki rice!

795
00:41:13,688 --> 00:41:15,334
Shirataki?

796
00:41:15,334 --> 00:41:17,214
Porridge.

797
00:41:17,214 --> 00:41:18,387
- Okay.
- Okay.

798
00:41:18,387 --> 00:41:20,727
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

799
00:41:26,912 --> 00:41:29,018
I wonder what it tastes like.

800
00:41:32,639 --> 00:41:33,842
This is good!

801
00:41:33,842 --> 00:41:35,382
Ji?

802
00:41:35,382 --> 00:41:37,395
Shirataki rice is...

803
00:41:37,395 --> 00:41:40,330
Like, it has zero carbs.

804
00:41:43,879 --> 00:41:47,238
Do Filipinos eat this porridge a lot?

805
00:41:47,238 --> 00:41:48,412
When you're hungover.

806
00:41:48,412 --> 00:41:49,496
When you're sick...

807
00:41:49,496 --> 00:41:51,582
Or when you're sick.

808
00:41:51,582 --> 00:41:54,562
I cooked this because I remember yesterday...

809
00:41:54,562 --> 00:41:57,109
You cooked kimchi...

810
00:41:57,109 --> 00:41:59,083
So I make, yeah.

811
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:02,415
So Filipino and Korean flavors are combined.

812
00:42:02,415 --> 00:42:04,761
So it's a fusion food.

813
00:42:04,761 --> 00:42:05,962
It's good.

814
00:42:05,962 --> 00:42:07,590
So good!

815
00:42:13,042 --> 00:42:15,005
The porridge is so good.

816
00:42:15,005 --> 00:42:16,684
- Good.
- Good.

817
00:42:16,684 --> 00:42:22,624
I think the lunch service today
went much smoother than yesterday.

818
00:42:22,624 --> 00:42:26,577
I personally think
the discussion we had yesterday

819
00:42:26,577 --> 00:42:30,576
about our strategy for today worked.

820
00:42:30,576 --> 00:42:34,263
That's why everything was seamless

821
00:42:34,263 --> 00:42:37,687
during the lunch service.

822
00:42:44,457 --> 00:42:46,475
- It's a bit warm from the cue.
- They're cold.

823
00:42:46,475 --> 00:42:48,032
- What?
- They're cold.

824
00:42:48,032 --> 00:42:49,533
You're cold?

825
00:42:52,053 --> 00:42:54,567
But it was colder when we first got here.

826
00:42:54,567 --> 00:42:55,801
- Yeah.
- Five days ago.

827
00:42:55,801 --> 00:42:57,225
Oh, really?

828
00:42:57,225 --> 00:43:00,228
It's like the temperature suddenly dropped.

829
00:43:00,228 --> 00:43:02,446
And all of a sudden, it became so cold.

830
00:43:02,446 --> 00:43:05,155
This is when the weather is nicest in Korea.

831
00:43:05,155 --> 00:43:07,001
- Now?
- Yes.

832
00:43:07,001 --> 00:43:08,436
Right now.

833
00:43:08,436 --> 00:43:09,887
Yeah.

834
00:43:09,887 --> 00:43:13,624
[As of Filming]
[Fall in Korea]

835
00:43:13,624 --> 00:43:17,394
[About 16~20°C]
[Perfect Weather for Koreans]

836
00:43:17,394 --> 00:43:21,031
[Nice Saturday Evening]

837
00:43:21,031 --> 00:43:23,234
[How chaotic will it be tonight?]

838
00:43:23,234 --> 00:43:26,036
Here comes the night again.

839
00:43:26,927 --> 00:43:28,045
Kumusta!

840
00:43:28,045 --> 00:43:30,313
Kumusta!

841
00:43:30,313 --> 00:43:31,804
Let's go! Good luck!

842
00:43:31,804 --> 00:43:33,394
We're going to do good today!

843
00:43:33,394 --> 00:43:35,791
I have a great feeling! Yeah.

844
00:43:35,791 --> 00:43:37,881
Okay, I'm making my own station here.

845
00:43:37,881 --> 00:43:39,483
- Let's do the sisig here.
- Okay.

846
00:43:39,483 --> 00:43:42,459
I'll put the sisig here.

847
00:43:42,459 --> 00:43:45,822
And then, I'll put the sizzling plates.

848
00:43:48,614 --> 00:43:50,767
These all go at the bottom, right?

849
00:43:50,767 --> 00:43:52,536
- Yes.
- Okay, so I'm doing it right.

850
00:43:52,536 --> 00:43:54,397
Yes, everything.

851
00:43:59,876 --> 00:44:02,257
We're good with the calamansi, Chef.

852
00:44:02,257 --> 00:44:03,474
- What else?
- Thank you.

853
00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:05,515
Your liver sauce is here.

854
00:44:05,515 --> 00:44:07,078
Garlic chips.

855
00:44:07,078 --> 00:44:11,549
You don't need this anymore,
so I'll clean this up.

856
00:44:11,549 --> 00:44:13,746
Thank you. You're the best.

857
00:44:13,746 --> 00:44:16,020
Thank you, Ji.

858
00:44:16,020 --> 00:44:18,889
[Kumusta Members Busy Preparing]

859
00:44:19,919 --> 00:44:20,998
Oh, here it is!

860
00:44:20,998 --> 00:44:22,992
I guess we just go in.

861
00:44:23,927 --> 00:44:28,966
[Two Mysterious Men Entering The Restaurant]

862
00:44:31,386 --> 00:44:33,488
Oh, it's nice!

863
00:44:33,488 --> 00:44:35,495
Wow, why is this place so nice?

864
00:44:35,495 --> 00:44:37,741
- What?
- I'm surprised!

865
00:44:38,326 --> 00:44:39,907
Oh my, oh my.

866
00:44:39,907 --> 00:44:42,686
Oh my, our staff.

867
00:44:42,686 --> 00:44:46,412
If we are lucky tomorrow,

868
00:44:46,412 --> 00:44:50,421
if we have more hands
or more people coming in to help us...

869
00:44:50,421 --> 00:44:53,096
- Oh well, we have one plus one.
- Yes.

870
00:44:53,096 --> 00:44:56,160
I'll try calling one or two people.

871
00:44:56,160 --> 00:44:58,802
Oh, that will be perfect.

872
00:44:59,468 --> 00:45:01,788
[Kim Myung Soo - Singer &amp; Actor]
Hello!

873
00:45:01,788 --> 00:45:03,123
- Hello!
- Hello!

874
00:45:03,123 --> 00:45:05,207
[Kim Min Seok - Actor]

875
00:45:07,055 --> 00:45:09,006
<i>Hi, baby.</i>

876
00:45:09,006 --> 00:45:11,125
<i>Where are you?</i>

877
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:14,078
<i>I'm in Korea, remember?</i>

878
00:45:14,078 --> 00:45:16,186
<i>Look at Mama's uniform!</i>

879
00:45:16,186 --> 00:45:17,815
<i>- What does it say?
- Mama's uniform.</i>

880
00:45:17,815 --> 00:45:19,684
<i>Kumusta!</i>

881
00:45:19,684 --> 00:45:21,747
<i>Mama, are you a chef?</i>

882
00:45:21,747 --> 00:45:23,599
<i>Yeah, I'm a chef right now.</i>

883
00:45:23,599 --> 00:45:25,779
<i>I'm cooking a lot of food.</i>

884
00:45:25,779 --> 00:45:27,569
<i>You want palabok?</i>

885
00:45:27,569 --> 00:45:30,478
<i>Yes, are you going to cook palabok there?</i>

886
00:45:30,478 --> 00:45:32,947
<i>Yeah, I cook a lot of palabok.</i>

887
00:45:32,947 --> 00:45:34,210
<i>- Jude, Jude, Jude!
- Yes.</i>

888
00:45:34,210 --> 00:45:35,661
<i>- You miss Mama?
- Yes.</i>

889
00:45:35,661 --> 00:45:36,661
<i>Yes.</i>

890
00:45:36,661 --> 00:45:39,002
<i>How much do you miss Mama?</i>

891
00:45:41,011 --> 00:45:42,223
<i>A lot!</i>

892
00:45:42,223 --> 00:45:43,296
<i>A lot?</i>

893
00:45:43,296 --> 00:45:46,175
<i>Me too, I miss you so much.</i>

894
00:45:48,235 --> 00:45:50,131
<i>Three sleeps!</i>

895
00:45:50,131 --> 00:45:51,165
<i>Three more sleeps.</i>

896
00:45:51,165 --> 00:45:53,884
<i>You sleep three more times
and then Mama will be home.</i>

897
00:45:53,884 --> 00:45:56,131
<i>- Okay?
- Okay!</i>

898
00:45:56,131 --> 00:45:58,421
<i>I love you!</i>

899
00:46:01,776 --> 00:46:03,994
<i>Okay, thank you.</i>

900
00:46:03,994 --> 00:46:06,630
<i>- Bye-bye.
- Bye.</i>

901
00:46:15,809 --> 00:46:17,309
<i>Okay.</i>

902
00:46:20,344 --> 00:46:23,146
<i>What a day...</i>
